        <Parent_String>Pinus (genus) [300343658], Pinaceae (family) [300343672], Pinales (order) [300343666], Pinopsida (class) [300343663], Coniferophyta (division) [300265702], Plantae (kingdom) [300132360], Eukaryota (domain) [300265677], living organisms (entities) [300390503], Living Organisms (hierarchy name) [300265673], Agents Facet [300264089]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of pine native to the eastern highlands of the island of Cuba. The closely related Hispaniolan pine (P. occidentalis), native to the neighboring island of Hispaniola, is treated as the same species as the Cuban pine in some classifications.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>松樹的種名，是古巴島上東部的高地原生種。在部分的分類法中，與其為近親的希斯盤紐拉杉樹（P. occidentalis，為鄰近的伊斯帕尼奧拉島(Hispaniola)的原生樹種）則被視為和古巴松同屬一個種的樹木。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pijnboomsoort die inheems is in de oostelijke hooglanden van Cuba. De daarmee nauw verwante Pina occidentalis, die voorkomt op het naburige eiland Hispaniola, wordt in sommige classificaties beschouwd als dezelfde soort als de Pina occidentalis.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
